7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This file contains a pass that expands pseudo instructions into target ----
10 // instructions to allow proper scheduling, if-conversion, and other late ----
11 // optimizations. This pass should be run after register allocation but before ----
12 // the post-regalloc scheduling pass. ----
13 // ----
14 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
15 ----

124 namespace { ----
125 // Constants for register spacing in NEON load/store instructions. ----
126 // For quad-register load-lane and store-lane pseudo instructors, the ----
127 // spacing is initially assumed to be EvenDblSpc, and that is changed to ----
128 // OddDblSpc depending on the lane number operand. ----
129 enum NEONRegSpacing { ----
130 SingleSpc, ----
131 SingleLowSpc , // Single spacing, low registers, three and four vectors. ----
132 SingleHighQSpc, // Single spacing, high registers, four vectors. ----
133 SingleHighTSpc, // Single spacing, high registers, three vectors. ----
134 EvenDblSpc, ----
135 OddDblSpc ----
136 }; ----
137 ----
138 // Entries for NEON load/store information table. The table is sorted by ----
139 // PseudoOpc for fast binary-search lookups. ----
140 struct NEONLdStTableEntry { ----
141 uint16_t PseudoOpc; ----
142 uint16_t RealOpc; ----
143 bool IsLoad; ----
144 bool isUpdating; ----
145 bool hasWritebackOperand; ----
146 uint8_t RegSpacing; // One of type NEONRegSpacing ----
147 uint8_t NumRegs; // D registers loaded or stored ----
148 uint8_t RegElts; // elements per D register; used for lane ops ----
149 // FIXME: Temporary flag to denote whether the real instruction takes ----
150 // a single register (like the encoding) or all of the registers in ----
151 // the list (like the asm syntax and the isel DAG). When all definitions ----
152 // are converted to take only the single encoded register, this will ----
153 // go away. ----
154 bool copyAllListRegs; ----
155 ----
156 // Comparison methods for binary search of the table. ----
157 bool operator<(const NEONLdStTableEntry &TE) const { 0
158 return PseudoOpc < TE.PseudoOpc; 0
159 } ----
160 friend bool operator<(const NEONLdStTableEntry &TE, unsigned PseudoOpc) { 0
161 return TE.PseudoOpc < PseudoOpc; 0
162 } ----
163 friend bool LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED operator<(unsigned PseudoOpc, ----
164 const NEONLdStTableEntry &TE) { ----
165 return PseudoOpc < TE.PseudoOpc; ----
166 } ----
167 }; ----
168 } ----
169 ----

497 /// LookupNEONLdSt - Search the NEONLdStTable for information about a NEON ----
498 /// load or store pseudo instruction. ----
499 static const NEONLdStTableEntry *LookupNEONLdSt(unsigned Opcode) { 0
500 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
501 // Make sure the table is sorted. ----
502 static std::atomic TableChecked(false); ----
503 if (!TableChecked.load(std::memory_order_relaxed)) { 0
504 assert(llvm::is_sorted(NEONLdStTable) && "NEONLdStTable is not sorted!"); 0
505 TableChecked.store(true, std::memory_order_relaxed); 0
506 } ----
507 #endif ----
508 ----
509 auto I = llvm::lower_bound(NEONLdStTable, Opcode); 0
510 if (I != std::end(NEONLdStTable) && I->PseudoOpc == Opcode) 0
511 return I; 0
512 return nullptr; 0
513 } ----
514 ----
515 /// GetDSubRegs - Get 4 D subregisters of a Q, QQ, or QQQQ register, ----
516 /// corresponding to the specified register spacing. Not all of the results ----
517 /// are necessarily valid, e.g., a Q register only has 2 D subregisters. ----
518 static void GetDSubRegs(unsigned Reg, NEONRegSpacing RegSpc, 0
519 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, unsigned &D0, ----
520 unsigned &D1, unsigned &D2, unsigned &D3) { ----
521 if (RegSpc == SingleSpc || RegSpc == SingleLowSpc) { 0
522 D0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_0); 0
523 D1 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_1); 0
524 D2 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_2); 0
525 D3 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_3); 0
526 } else if (RegSpc == SingleHighQSpc) { 0
527 D0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_4); 0
528 D1 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_5); 0
529 D2 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_6); 0
530 D3 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_7); 0
531 } else if (RegSpc == SingleHighTSpc) { 0
532 D0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_3); 0
533 D1 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_4); 0
534 D2 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_5); 0
535 D3 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_6); 0
536 } else if (RegSpc == EvenDblSpc) { 0
537 D0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_0); 0
538 D1 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_2); 0
539 D2 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_4); 0
540 D3 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_6); 0
541 } else { ----
542 assert(RegSpc == OddDblSpc && "unknown register spacing"); 0
543 D0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_1); 0
544 D1 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_3); 0
545 D2 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_5); 0
546 D3 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_7); 0
547 } ----
548 } 0
549 ----
550 /// ExpandVLD - Translate VLD pseudo instructions with Q, QQ or QQQQ register ----
551 /// operands to real VLD instructions with D register operands. ----
552 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandVLD(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { 0
553 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
554 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
555 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
556 ----
557 const NEONLdStTableEntry *TableEntry = LookupNEONLdSt(MI.getOpcode()); 0
558 assert(TableEntry && TableEntry->IsLoad && "NEONLdStTable lookup failed"); 0
559 NEONRegSpacing RegSpc = (NEONRegSpacing)TableEntry->RegSpacing; 0
560 unsigned NumRegs = TableEntry->NumRegs; 0
561 ----
562 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
563 TII->get(TableEntry->RealOpc)); 0
564 unsigned OpIdx = 0; 0
565 ----
566 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(OpIdx).isDead(); 0
567 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++).getReg(); 0
568 ----
569 bool IsVLD2DUP = TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd8x2 || 0
570 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd16x2 || 0
571 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd32x2 || 0
572 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd8x2wb_fixed || 0
573 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd16x2wb_fixed || 0
574 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd32x2wb_fixed || 0
575 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd8x2wb_register || 0
576 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd16x2wb_register || 0
577 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd32x2wb_register; 0
578 ----
579 if (IsVLD2DUP) { 0
580 unsigned SubRegIndex; ----
581 if (RegSpc == EvenDblSpc) { 0
582 SubRegIndex = ARM::dsub_0; 0
583 } else { ----
584 assert(RegSpc == OddDblSpc && "Unexpected spacing!"); 0
585 SubRegIndex = ARM::dsub_1; 0
586 } ----
587 Register SubReg = TRI->getSubReg(DstReg, SubRegIndex); 0
588 unsigned DstRegPair = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(SubReg, ARM::dsub_0, 0
589 &ARM::DPairSpcRegClass); 0
590 MIB.addReg(DstRegPair, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
591 } else { ----
592 unsigned D0, D1, D2, D3; ----
593 GetDSubRegs(DstReg, RegSpc, TRI, D0, D1, D2, D3); 0
594 MIB.addReg(D0, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
595 if (NumRegs > 1 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
596 MIB.addReg(D1, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
597 if (NumRegs > 2 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
598 MIB.addReg(D2, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
599 if (NumRegs > 3 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
600 MIB.addReg(D3, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
601 } ----
602 ----
603 if (TableEntry->isUpdating) 0
604 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
605 ----
606 // Copy the addrmode6 operands. ----
607 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
608 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
609 ----
610 // Copy the am6offset operand. ----
611 if (TableEntry->hasWritebackOperand) { 0
612 // TODO: The writing-back pseudo instructions we translate here are all ----
613 // defined to take am6offset nodes that are capable to represent both fixed ----
614 // and register forms. Some real instructions, however, do not rely on ----
615 // am6offset and have separate definitions for such forms. When this is the ----
616 // case, fixed forms do not take any offset nodes, so here we skip them for ----
617 // such instructions. Once all real and pseudo writing-back instructions are ----
618 // rewritten without use of am6offset nodes, this code will go away. ----
619 const MachineOperand &AM6Offset = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++); 0
620 if (TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d8Qwb_fixed || 0
621 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d16Qwb_fixed || 0
622 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d32Qwb_fixed || 0
623 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d64Qwb_fixed || 0
624 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d8Twb_fixed || 0
625 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d16Twb_fixed || 0
626 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d32Twb_fixed || 0
627 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD1d64Twb_fixed || 0
628 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd8x2wb_fixed || 0
629 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd16x2wb_fixed || 0
630 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VLD2DUPd32x2wb_fixed) { 0
631 assert(AM6Offset.getReg() == 0 && 0
632 "A fixed writing-back pseudo instruction provides an offset " ----
633 "register!"); ----
634 } else { ----
635 MIB.add(AM6Offset); 0
636 } ----
637 } ----
638 ----
639 // For an instruction writing double-spaced subregs, the pseudo instruction ----
640 // has an extra operand that is a use of the super-register. Record the ----
641 // operand index and skip over it. ----
642 unsigned SrcOpIdx = 0; 0
643 if (!IsVLD2DUP) { 0
644 if (RegSpc == EvenDblSpc || RegSpc == OddDblSpc || 0
645 RegSpc == SingleLowSpc || RegSpc == SingleHighQSpc || 0
646 RegSpc == SingleHighTSpc) ----
647 SrcOpIdx = OpIdx++; 0
648 } ----
649 ----
650 // Copy the predicate operands. ----
651 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
652 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
653 ----
654 // Copy the super-register source operand used for double-spaced subregs over ----
655 // to the new instruction as an implicit operand. ----
656 if (SrcOpIdx != 0) { 0
657 MachineOperand MO = MI.getOperand(SrcOpIdx); 0
658 MO.setImplicit(true); 0
659 MIB.add(MO); 0
660 } ----
661 // Add an implicit def for the super-register. ----
662 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::ImplicitDefine | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
663 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
664 ----
665 // Transfer memoperands. ----
666 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
667 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
668 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "To: "; MIB.getInstr()->dump();); 0
669 } 0
670 ----
671 /// ExpandVST - Translate VST pseudo instructions with Q, QQ or QQQQ register ----
672 /// operands to real VST instructions with D register operands. ----
673 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandVST(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { 0
674 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
675 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
676 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
677 ----
678 const NEONLdStTableEntry *TableEntry = LookupNEONLdSt(MI.getOpcode()); 0
679 assert(TableEntry && !TableEntry->IsLoad && "NEONLdStTable lookup failed"); 0
680 NEONRegSpacing RegSpc = (NEONRegSpacing)TableEntry->RegSpacing; 0
681 unsigned NumRegs = TableEntry->NumRegs; 0
682 ----
683 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
684 TII->get(TableEntry->RealOpc)); 0
685 unsigned OpIdx = 0; 0
686 if (TableEntry->isUpdating) 0
687 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
688 ----
689 // Copy the addrmode6 operands. ----
690 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
691 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
692 ----
693 if (TableEntry->hasWritebackOperand) { 0
694 // TODO: The writing-back pseudo instructions we translate here are all ----
695 // defined to take am6offset nodes that are capable to represent both fixed ----
696 // and register forms. Some real instructions, however, do not rely on ----
697 // am6offset and have separate definitions for such forms. When this is the ----
698 // case, fixed forms do not take any offset nodes, so here we skip them for ----
699 // such instructions. Once all real and pseudo writing-back instructions are ----
700 // rewritten without use of am6offset nodes, this code will go away. ----
701 const MachineOperand &AM6Offset = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++); 0
702 if (TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d8Qwb_fixed || 0
703 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d16Qwb_fixed || 0
704 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d32Qwb_fixed || 0
705 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d64Qwb_fixed || 0
706 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d8Twb_fixed || 0
707 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d16Twb_fixed || 0
708 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d32Twb_fixed || 0
709 TableEntry->RealOpc == ARM::VST1d64Twb_fixed) { 0
710 assert(AM6Offset.getReg() == 0 && 0
711 "A fixed writing-back pseudo instruction provides an offset " ----
712 "register!"); ----
713 } else { ----
714 MIB.add(AM6Offset); 0
715 } ----
716 } ----
717 ----
718 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(OpIdx).isKill(); 0
719 bool SrcIsUndef = MI.getOperand(OpIdx).isUndef(); 0
720 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++).getReg(); 0
721 unsigned D0, D1, D2, D3; ----
722 GetDSubRegs(SrcReg, RegSpc, TRI, D0, D1, D2, D3); 0
723 MIB.addReg(D0, getUndefRegState(SrcIsUndef)); 0
724 if (NumRegs > 1 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
725 MIB.addReg(D1, getUndefRegState(SrcIsUndef)); 0
726 if (NumRegs > 2 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
727 MIB.addReg(D2, getUndefRegState(SrcIsUndef)); 0
728 if (NumRegs > 3 && TableEntry->copyAllListRegs) 0
729 MIB.addReg(D3, getUndefRegState(SrcIsUndef)); 0
730 ----
731 // Copy the predicate operands. ----
732 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
733 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
734 ----
735 if (SrcIsKill && !SrcIsUndef) // Add an implicit kill for the super-reg. 0
736 MIB->addRegisterKilled(SrcReg, TRI, true); 0
737 else if (!SrcIsUndef) 0
738 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit); // Add implicit uses for src reg. 0
739 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
740 ----
741 // Transfer memoperands. ----
742 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
743 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
744 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "To: "; MIB.getInstr()->dump();); 0
745 } 0
746 ----
747 /// ExpandLaneOp - Translate VLD*LN and VST*LN instructions with Q, QQ or QQQQ ----
748 /// register operands to real instructions with D register operands. ----
749 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandLaneOp(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { 0
750 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
751 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
752 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
753 ----
754 const NEONLdStTableEntry *TableEntry = LookupNEONLdSt(MI.getOpcode()); 0
755 assert(TableEntry && "NEONLdStTable lookup failed"); 0
756 NEONRegSpacing RegSpc = (NEONRegSpacing)TableEntry->RegSpacing; 0
757 unsigned NumRegs = TableEntry->NumRegs; 0
758 unsigned RegElts = TableEntry->RegElts; 0
759 ----
760 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
761 TII->get(TableEntry->RealOpc)); 0
762 unsigned OpIdx = 0; 0
763 // The lane operand is always the 3rd from last operand, before the 2 ----
764 // predicate operands. ----
765 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(MI.getDesc().getNumOperands() - 3).getImm(); 0
766 ----
767 // Adjust the lane and spacing as needed for Q registers. ----
768 assert(RegSpc != OddDblSpc && "unexpected register spacing for VLD/VST-lane"); 0
769 if (RegSpc == EvenDblSpc && Lane >= RegElts) { 0
770 RegSpc = OddDblSpc; 0
771 Lane -= RegElts; 0
772 } ----
773 assert(Lane < RegElts && "out of range lane for VLD/VST-lane"); 0
774 ----
775 unsigned D0 = 0, D1 = 0, D2 = 0, D3 = 0; 0
776 unsigned DstReg = 0; 0
777 bool DstIsDead = false; 0
778 if (TableEntry->IsLoad) { 0
779 DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(OpIdx).isDead(); 0
780 DstReg = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++).getReg(); 0
781 GetDSubRegs(DstReg, RegSpc, TRI, D0, D1, D2, D3); 0
782 MIB.addReg(D0, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
783 if (NumRegs > 1) 0
784 MIB.addReg(D1, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
785 if (NumRegs > 2) 0
786 MIB.addReg(D2, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
787 if (NumRegs > 3) 0
788 MIB.addReg(D3, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
789 } ----
790 ----
791 if (TableEntry->isUpdating) 0
792 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
793 ----
794 // Copy the addrmode6 operands. ----
795 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
796 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
797 // Copy the am6offset operand. ----
798 if (TableEntry->hasWritebackOperand) 0
799 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
800 ----
801 // Grab the super-register source. ----
802 MachineOperand MO = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++); 0
803 if (!TableEntry->IsLoad) 0
804 GetDSubRegs(MO.getReg(), RegSpc, TRI, D0, D1, D2, D3); 0
805 ----
806 // Add the subregs as sources of the new instruction. ----
807 unsigned SrcFlags = (getUndefRegState(MO.isUndef()) | 0
808 getKillRegState(MO.isKill())); 0
809 MIB.addReg(D0, SrcFlags); 0
810 if (NumRegs > 1) 0
811 MIB.addReg(D1, SrcFlags); 0
812 if (NumRegs > 2) 0
813 MIB.addReg(D2, SrcFlags); 0
814 if (NumRegs > 3) 0
815 MIB.addReg(D3, SrcFlags); 0
816 ----
817 // Add the lane number operand. ----
818 MIB.addImm(Lane); 0
819 OpIdx += 1; 0
820 ----
821 // Copy the predicate operands. ----
822 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
823 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
824 ----
825 // Copy the super-register source to be an implicit source. ----
826 MO.setImplicit(true); 0
827 MIB.add(MO); 0
828 if (TableEntry->IsLoad) 0
829 // Add an implicit def for the super-register. ----
830 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::ImplicitDefine | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
831 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
832 // Transfer memoperands. ----
833 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
834 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
835 } 0

837 /// ExpandVTBL - Translate VTBL and VTBX pseudo instructions with Q or QQ ----
838 /// register operands to real instructions with D register operands. ----
839 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandVTBL(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI, 0
840 unsigned Opc, bool IsExt) { ----
841 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
842 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
843 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
844 ----
845 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)); 0
846 unsigned OpIdx = 0; 0
847 ----
848 // Transfer the destination register operand. ----
849 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
850 if (IsExt) { 0
851 MachineOperand VdSrc(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
852 MIB.add(VdSrc); 0
853 } ----
854 ----
855 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(OpIdx).isKill(); 0
856 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(OpIdx++).getReg(); 0
857 unsigned D0, D1, D2, D3; ----
858 GetDSubRegs(SrcReg, SingleSpc, TRI, D0, D1, D2, D3); 0
859 MIB.addReg(D0); 0
860 ----
861 // Copy the other source register operand. ----
862 MachineOperand VmSrc(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
863 MIB.add(VmSrc); 0
864 ----
865 // Copy the predicate operands. ----
866 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
867 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(OpIdx++)); 0
868 ----
869 // Add an implicit kill and use for the super-reg. ----
870 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit | getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
871 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
872 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
873 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "To: "; MIB.getInstr()->dump();); 0
874 } 0
875 ----
876 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandMQQPRLoadStore(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { 0
877 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
878 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
879 unsigned NewOpc = ----
880 MI.getOpcode() == ARM::MQQPRStore || MI.getOpcode() == ARM::MQQQQPRStore 0
881 ? ARM::VSTMDIA 0
882 : ARM::VLDMDIA; 0
883 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
884 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)); 0
885 ----
886 unsigned Flags = getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(0).isKill()) | 0
887 getDefRegState(MI.getOperand(0).isDef()); 0
888 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
889 ----
890 // Copy the destination register. ----
891 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
892 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
893 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_0), Flags); 0
894 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_1), Flags); 0
895 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_2), Flags); 0
896 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_3), Flags); 0
897 if (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::MQQQQPRStore || 0
898 MI.getOpcode() == ARM::MQQQQPRLoad) { 0
899 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_4), Flags); 0
900 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_5), Flags); 0
901 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_6), Flags); 0
902 MIB.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(SrcReg, ARM::dsub_7), Flags); 0
903 } ----
904 ----
905 if (NewOpc == ARM::VSTMDIA) 0
906 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit); 0
907 ----
908 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
909 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
910 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
911 } 0
912 ----
913 static bool IsAnAddressOperand(const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
914 // This check is overly conservative. Unless we are certain that the machine ----
915 // operand is not a symbol reference, we return that it is a symbol reference. ----
916 // This is important as the load pair may not be split up Windows. ----
917 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
918 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: 0
919 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: ----
920 case MachineOperand::MO_CImmediate: ----
921 case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: ----
922 case MachineOperand::MO_ShuffleMask: ----
923 return false; 0
924 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
925 return true; 0
926 case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex: 0
927 return false; 0
928 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
929 case MachineOperand::MO_TargetIndex: ----
930 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: ----
931 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: ----
932 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: ----
933 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: ----
934 return true; 0
935 case MachineOperand::MO_RegisterMask: 0
936 case MachineOperand::MO_RegisterLiveOut: ----
937 return false; 0
938 case MachineOperand::MO_Metadata: 0
939 case MachineOperand::MO_MCSymbol: ----
940 return true; 0
941 case MachineOperand::MO_DbgInstrRef: 0
942 case MachineOperand::MO_CFIIndex: ----
943 return false; 0
944 case MachineOperand::MO_IntrinsicID: 0
945 case MachineOperand::MO_Predicate: ----
946 llvm_unreachable("should not exist post-isel"); 0
947 } ----
948 llvm_unreachable("unhandled machine operand type"); 0
949 } ----
950 ----
951 static MachineOperand makeImplicit(const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
952 MachineOperand NewMO = MO; 0
953 NewMO.setImplicit(); 0
954 return NewMO; 0
955 } ----
956 ----
957 static MachineOperand getMovOperand(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
958 unsigned TargetFlag) { ----
959 unsigned TF = MO.getTargetFlags() | TargetFlag; 0
960 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
961 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
962 unsigned Imm = MO.getImm(); 0
963 switch (TargetFlag) { ----
964 case ARMII::MO_HI_8_15: 0
965 Imm = (Imm >> 24) & 0xff; 0
966 break; 0
967 case ARMII::MO_HI_0_7: 0
968 Imm = (Imm >> 16) & 0xff; 0
969 break; 0
970 case ARMII::MO_LO_8_15: 0
971 Imm = (Imm >> 8) & 0xff; 0
972 break; 0
973 case ARMII::MO_LO_0_7: 0
974 Imm = Imm & 0xff; 0
975 break; 0
976 case ARMII::MO_HI16: 0
977 Imm = (Imm >> 16) & 0xffff; 0
978 break; 0
979 case ARMII::MO_LO16: 0
980 Imm = Imm & 0xffff; 0
981 break; 0
982 default: 0
983 llvm_unreachable("Only HI/LO target flags are expected"); 0
984 } ----
985 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(Imm); 0
986 } ----
987 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: 0
988 return MachineOperand::CreateES(MO.getSymbolName(), TF); 0
989 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: 0
990 return MachineOperand::CreateJTI(MO.getIndex(), TF); 0
991 default: 0
992 return MachineOperand::CreateGA(MO.getGlobal(), MO.getOffset(), TF); 0
993 } ----
994 } ----
995 ----
996 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandTMOV32BitImm(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
997 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
998 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
999 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1000 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1001 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(1); 0
1002 unsigned MIFlags = MI.getFlags(); 0
1003 ----
1004 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
1005 ----
1006 // Expand the mov into a sequence of mov/add+lsl of the individual bytes. We ----
1007 // want to avoid emitting any zero bytes, as they won't change the result, and ----
1008 // also don't want any pointless shifts, so instead of immediately emitting ----
1009 // the shift for a byte we keep track of how much we will need to shift and do ----
1010 // it before the next nonzero byte. ----
1011 unsigned PendingShift = 0; 0
1012 for (unsigned Byte = 0; Byte < 4; ++Byte) { 0
1013 unsigned Flag = Byte == 0 ? ARMII::MO_HI_8_15 0
1014 : Byte == 1 ? ARMII::MO_HI_0_7 ----
1015 : Byte == 2 ? ARMII::MO_LO_8_15 ----
1016 : ARMII::MO_LO_0_7; ----
1017 MachineOperand Operand = getMovOperand(MO, Flag); 0
1018 bool ZeroImm = Operand.isImm() && Operand.getImm() == 0; 0
1019 unsigned Op = PendingShift ? ARM::tADDi8 : ARM::tMOVi8; 0
1020 ----
1021 // Emit the pending shift if we're going to emit this byte or if we've ----
1022 // reached the end. ----
1023 if (PendingShift && (!ZeroImm || Byte == 3)) { 0
1024 MachineInstr *Lsl = ----
1025 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::tLSLri), DstReg) 0
1026 .add(t1CondCodeOp(true)) 0
1027 .addReg(DstReg) 0
1028 .addImm(PendingShift) 0
1029 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1030 .setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1031 (void)Lsl; ----
1032 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "And: "; Lsl->dump();); 0
1033 PendingShift = 0; 0
1034 } ----
1035 ----
1036 // Emit this byte if it's nonzero. ----
1037 if (!ZeroImm) { 0
1038 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1039 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Op), DstReg) 0
1040 .add(t1CondCodeOp(true)); 0
1041 if (Op == ARM::tADDi8) 0
1042 MIB.addReg(DstReg); 0
1043 MIB.add(Operand); 0
1044 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1045 MIB.setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1046 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (Op == ARM::tMOVi8 ? "To: " : "And:") << " "; 0
1047 MIB.getInstr()->dump();); ----
1048 } ----
1049 ----
1050 // Don't accumulate the shift value if we've not yet seen a nonzero byte. ----
1051 if (PendingShift || !ZeroImm) 0
1052 PendingShift += 8; 0
1053 } ----
1054 ----
1055 // The dest is dead on the last instruction we emitted if it was dead on the ----
1056 // original instruction. ----
1057 (--MBBI)->getOperand(0).setIsDead(DstIsDead); 0
1058 ----
1059 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1060 } 0
1061 ----
1062 void ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandMOV32BitImm(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1063 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
1064 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1065 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1066 Register PredReg; 0
1067 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(MI, PredReg); 0
1068 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1069 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1070 bool isCC = Opcode == ARM::MOVCCi32imm || Opcode == ARM::t2MOVCCi32imm; 0
1071 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(isCC ? 2 : 1); 0
1072 bool RequiresBundling = STI->isTargetWindows() && IsAnAddressOperand(MO); 0
1073 MachineInstrBuilder LO16, HI16; 0
1074 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding: "; MI.dump()); 0
1075 ----
1076 if (!STI->hasV6T2Ops() && 0
1077 (Opcode == ARM::MOVi32imm || Opcode == ARM::MOVCCi32imm)) { 0
1078 // FIXME Windows CE supports older ARM CPUs ----
1079 assert(!STI->isTargetWindows() && "Windows on ARM requires ARMv7+"); 0
1080 ----
1081 assert (MO.isImm() && "MOVi32imm w/ non-immediate source operand!"); 0
1082 unsigned ImmVal = (unsigned)MO.getImm(); 0
1083 unsigned SOImmValV1 = 0, SOImmValV2 = 0; 0
1084 ----
1085 if (ARM_AM::isSOImmTwoPartVal(ImmVal)) { // Expand into a movi + orr. 0
1086 LO16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::MOVi), DstReg); 0
1087 HI16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::ORRri)) 0
1088 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1089 .addReg(DstReg); 0
1090 SOImmValV1 = ARM_AM::getSOImmTwoPartFirst(ImmVal); 0
1091 SOImmValV2 = ARM_AM::getSOImmTwoPartSecond(ImmVal); 0
1092 } else { // Expand into a mvn + sub. ----
1093 LO16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::MVNi), DstReg); 0
1094 HI16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::SUBri)) 0
1095 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1096 .addReg(DstReg); 0
1097 SOImmValV1 = ARM_AM::getSOImmTwoPartFirst(-ImmVal); 0
1098 SOImmValV2 = ARM_AM::getSOImmTwoPartSecond(-ImmVal); 0
1099 SOImmValV1 = ~(-SOImmValV1); 0
1100 } ----
1101 ----
1102 unsigned MIFlags = MI.getFlags(); 0
1103 LO16 = LO16.addImm(SOImmValV1); 0
1104 HI16 = HI16.addImm(SOImmValV2); 0
1105 LO16.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1106 HI16.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1107 LO16.setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1108 HI16.setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1109 LO16.addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg).add(condCodeOp()); 0
1110 HI16.addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg).add(condCodeOp()); 0
1111 if (isCC) 0
1112 LO16.add(makeImplicit(MI.getOperand(1))); 0
1113 LO16.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
1114 HI16.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
1115 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1116 return; 0
1117 } ----
1118 ----
1119 unsigned LO16Opc = 0; 0
1120 unsigned HI16Opc = 0; 0
1121 unsigned MIFlags = MI.getFlags(); 0
1122 if (Opcode == ARM::t2MOVi32imm || Opcode == ARM::t2MOVCCi32imm) { 0
1123 LO16Opc = ARM::t2MOVi16; 0
1124 HI16Opc = ARM::t2MOVTi16; 0
1125 } else { ----
1126 LO16Opc = ARM::MOVi16; 0
1127 HI16Opc = ARM::MOVTi16; 0
1128 } ----
1129 ----
1130 LO16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(LO16Opc), DstReg); 0
1131 LO16.setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1132 LO16.add(getMovOperand(MO, ARMII::MO_LO16)); 0
1133 LO16.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1134 LO16.addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1135 if (isCC) 0
1136 LO16.add(makeImplicit(MI.getOperand(1))); 0
1137 LO16.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
1138 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "To: "; LO16.getInstr()->dump();); 0
1139 ----
1140 MachineOperand HIOperand = getMovOperand(MO, ARMII::MO_HI16); 0
1141 if (!(HIOperand.isImm() && HIOperand.getImm() == 0)) { 0
1142 HI16 = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(HI16Opc)) 0
1143 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1144 .addReg(DstReg); 0
1145 HI16.setMIFlags(MIFlags); 0
1146 HI16.add(HIOperand); 0
1147 HI16.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1148 HI16.addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1149 HI16.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
1150 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "And: "; HI16.getInstr()->dump();); 0
1151 } else { ----
1152 LO16->getOperand(0).setIsDead(DstIsDead); 0
1153 } ----
1154 ----
1155 if (RequiresBundling) 0
1156 finalizeBundle(MBB, LO16->getIterator(), MBBI->getIterator()); 0
1157 ----
1158 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 // The size of the area, accessed by that VLSTM/VLLDM ----
1162 // S0-S31 + FPSCR + 8 more bytes (VPR + pad, or just pad) ----
1163 static const int CMSE_FP_SAVE_SIZE = 136; ----
1164 ----
1165 static void determineGPRegsToClear(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1166 const std::initializer_list &Regs, ----
1167 SmallVectorImpl &ClearRegs) { ----
1168 SmallVector OpRegs; 0
1169 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.operands()) { 0
1170 if (!Op.isReg() || !Op.isUse()) 0
1171 continue; 0
1172 OpRegs.push_back(Op.getReg()); 0
1173 } ----
1174 llvm::sort(OpRegs); 0
1175 ----
1176 std::set_difference(Regs.begin(), Regs.end(), OpRegs.begin(), OpRegs.end(), 0
1177 std::back_inserter(ClearRegs)); ----
1178 } 0
1179 ----
1180 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSEClearGPRegs( 0
1181 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1182 const DebugLoc &DL, const SmallVectorImpl &ClearRegs, ----
1183 unsigned ClobberReg) { ----
1184 ----
1185 if (STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps()) { 0
1186 // Clear the registers using the CLRM instruction. ----
1187 MachineInstrBuilder CLRM = ----
1188 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2CLRM)).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1189 for (unsigned R : ClearRegs) 0
1190 CLRM.addReg(R, RegState::Define); 0
1191 CLRM.addReg(ARM::APSR, RegState::Define); 0
1192 CLRM.addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Define | RegState::Implicit); 0
1193 } else { ----
1194 // Clear the registers and flags by copying ClobberReg into them. ----
1195 // (Baseline can't do a high register clear in one instruction). ----
1196 for (unsigned Reg : ClearRegs) { 0
1197 if (Reg == ClobberReg) 0
1198 continue; 0
1199 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tMOVr), Reg) 0
1200 .addReg(ClobberReg) 0
1201 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1202 } ----
1203 ----
1204 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2MSR_M)) 0
1205 .addImm(STI->hasDSP() ? 0xc00 : 0x800) 0
1206 .addReg(ClobberReg) 0
1207 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1208 } ----
1209 } 0
1210 ----
1211 // Find which FP registers need to be cleared. The parameter `ClearRegs` is ----
1212 // initialised with all elements set to true, and this function resets all the ----
1213 // bits, which correspond to register uses. Returns true if any floating point ----
1214 // register is defined, false otherwise. ----
1215 static bool determineFPRegsToClear(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1216 BitVector &ClearRegs) { ----
1217 bool DefFP = false; 0
1218 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.operands()) { 0
1219 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1220 continue; 0
1221 ----
1222 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1223 if (Op.isDef()) { 0
1224 if ((Reg >= ARM::Q0 && Reg <= ARM::Q7) || 0
1225 (Reg >= ARM::D0 && Reg <= ARM::D15) || 0
1226 (Reg >= ARM::S0 && Reg <= ARM::S31)) 0
1227 DefFP = true; 0
1228 continue; 0
1229 } ----
1230 ----
1231 if (Reg >= ARM::Q0 && Reg <= ARM::Q7) { 0
1232 int R = Reg - ARM::Q0; 0
1233 ClearRegs.reset(R * 4, (R + 1) * 4); 0
1234 } else if (Reg >= ARM::D0 && Reg <= ARM::D15) { 0
1235 int R = Reg - ARM::D0; 0
1236 ClearRegs.reset(R * 2, (R + 1) * 2); 0
1237 } else if (Reg >= ARM::S0 && Reg <= ARM::S31) { 0
1238 ClearRegs[Reg - ARM::S0] = false; 0
1239 } ----
1240 } ----
1241 return DefFP; 0
1242 } ----
1243 ----
1244 MachineBasicBlock & ----
1245 ARMExpandPseudo::CMSEClearFPRegs(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1246 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
1247 BitVector ClearRegs(16, true); 0
1248 (void)determineFPRegsToClear(*MBBI, ClearRegs); 0
1249 ----
1250 if (STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps()) 0
1251 return CMSEClearFPRegsV81(MBB, MBBI, ClearRegs); 0
1252 else ----
1253 return CMSEClearFPRegsV8(MBB, MBBI, ClearRegs); 0
1254 } 0
1255 ----
1256 // Clear the FP registers for v8.0-M, by copying over the content ----
1257 // of LR. Uses R12 as a scratch register. ----
1258 MachineBasicBlock & ----
1259 ARMExpandPseudo::CMSEClearFPRegsV8(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1260 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1261 const BitVector &ClearRegs) { ----
1262 if (!STI->hasFPRegs()) 0
1263 return MBB; 0
1264 ----
1265 auto &RetI = *MBBI; 0
1266 const DebugLoc &DL = RetI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1267 ----
1268 // If optimising for minimum size, clear FP registers unconditionally. ----
1269 // Otherwise, check the CONTROL.SFPA (Secure Floating-Point Active) bit and ----
1270 // don't clear them if they belong to the non-secure state. ----
1271 MachineBasicBlock *ClearBB, *DoneBB; ----
1272 if (STI->hasMinSize()) { 0
1273 ClearBB = DoneBB = &MBB; 0
1274 } else { ----
1275 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
1276 ClearBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1277 DoneBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1278 ----
1279 MF->insert(++MBB.getIterator(), ClearBB); 0
1280 MF->insert(++ClearBB->getIterator(), DoneBB); 0
1281 ----
1282 DoneBB->splice(DoneBB->end(), &MBB, MBBI, MBB.end()); 0
1283 DoneBB->transferSuccessors(&MBB); 0
1284 MBB.addSuccessor(ClearBB); 0
1285 MBB.addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
1286 ClearBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
1287 ----
1288 // At the new basic blocks we need to have live-in the registers, used ----
1289 // for the return value as well as LR, used to clear registers. ----
1290 for (const MachineOperand &Op : RetI.operands()) { 0
1291 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1292 continue; 0
1293 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1294 if (Reg == ARM::NoRegister || Reg == ARM::LR) 0
1295 continue; 0
1296 assert(Reg.isPhysical() && "Unallocated register"); 0
1297 ClearBB->addLiveIn(Reg); 0
1298 DoneBB->addLiveIn(Reg); 0
1299 } ----
1300 ClearBB->addLiveIn(ARM::LR); 0
1301 DoneBB->addLiveIn(ARM::LR); 0
1302 ----
1303 // Read the CONTROL register. ----
1304 BuildMI(MBB, MBB.end(), DL, TII->get(ARM::t2MRS_M), ARM::R12) 0
1305 .addImm(20) 0
1306 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1307 // Check bit 3 (SFPA). ----
1308 BuildMI(MBB, MBB.end(), DL, TII->get(ARM::t2TSTri)) 0
1309 .addReg(ARM::R12) 0
1310 .addImm(8) 0
1311 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1312 // If SFPA is clear, jump over ClearBB to DoneBB. ----
1313 BuildMI(MBB, MBB.end(), DL, TII->get(ARM::tBcc)) 0
1314 .addMBB(DoneBB) 0
1315 .addImm(ARMCC::EQ) 0
1316 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
1317 } ----
1318 ----
1319 // Emit the clearing sequence ----
1320 for (unsigned D = 0; D < 8; D++) { 0
1321 // Attempt to clear as double ----
1322 if (ClearRegs[D * 2 + 0] && ClearRegs[D * 2 + 1]) { 0
1323 unsigned Reg = ARM::D0 + D; 0
1324 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVDRR), Reg) 0
1325 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1326 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1327 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1328 } else { ----
1329 // Clear first part as single ----
1330 if (ClearRegs[D * 2 + 0]) { 0
1331 unsigned Reg = ARM::S0 + D * 2; 0
1332 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVSR), Reg) 0
1333 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1334 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1335 } ----
1336 // Clear second part as single ----
1337 if (ClearRegs[D * 2 + 1]) { 0
1338 unsigned Reg = ARM::S0 + D * 2 + 1; 0
1339 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVSR), Reg) 0
1340 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1341 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1342 } ----
1343 } ----
1344 } ----
1345 ----
1346 // Clear FPSCR bits 0-4, 7, 28-31 ----
1347 // The other bits are program global according to the AAPCS ----
1348 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMRS), ARM::R12) 0
1349 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1350 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2BICri), ARM::R12) 0
1351 .addReg(ARM::R12) 0
1352 .addImm(0x0000009F) 0
1353 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1354 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
1355 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2BICri), ARM::R12) 0
1356 .addReg(ARM::R12) 0
1357 .addImm(0xF0000000) 0
1358 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1359 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
1360 BuildMI(ClearBB, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMSR)) 0
1361 .addReg(ARM::R12) 0
1362 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1363 ----
1364 return *DoneBB; 0
1365 } ----
1366 ----
1367 MachineBasicBlock & ----
1368 ARMExpandPseudo::CMSEClearFPRegsV81(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1369 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1370 const BitVector &ClearRegs) { ----
1371 auto &RetI = *MBBI; 0
1372 ----
1373 // Emit a sequence of VSCCLRM instructions, one instruction for ----
1374 // each contiguous sequence of S-registers. ----
1375 int Start = -1, End = -1; 0
1376 for (int S = 0, E = ClearRegs.size(); S != E; ++S) { 0
1377 if (ClearRegs[S] && S == End + 1) { 0
1378 End = S; // extend range 0
1379 continue; 0
1380 } ----
1381 // Emit current range. ----
1382 if (Start < End) { 0
1383 MachineInstrBuilder VSCCLRM = ----
1384 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, RetI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::VSCCLRMS)) 0
1385 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1386 while (++Start <= End) 0
1387 VSCCLRM.addReg(ARM::S0 + Start, RegState::Define); 0
1388 VSCCLRM.addReg(ARM::VPR, RegState::Define); 0
1389 } ----
1390 Start = End = S; 0
1391 } ----
1392 // Emit last range. ----
1393 if (Start < End) { 0
1394 MachineInstrBuilder VSCCLRM = ----
1395 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, RetI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::VSCCLRMS)) 0
1396 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1397 while (++Start <= End) 0
1398 VSCCLRM.addReg(ARM::S0 + Start, RegState::Define); 0
1399 VSCCLRM.addReg(ARM::VPR, RegState::Define); 0
1400 } ----
1401 ----
1402 return MBB; 0
1403 } ----
1404 ----
1405 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSESaveClearFPRegs( 0
1406 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, DebugLoc &DL, ----
1407 const LivePhysRegs &LiveRegs, SmallVectorImpl &ScratchRegs) { ----
1408 if (STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps()) 0
1409 CMSESaveClearFPRegsV81(MBB, MBBI, DL, LiveRegs); 0
1410 else if (STI->hasV8MMainlineOps()) 0
1411 CMSESaveClearFPRegsV8(MBB, MBBI, DL, LiveRegs, ScratchRegs); 0
1412 } 0
1413 ----
1414 // Save and clear FP registers if present ----
1415 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSESaveClearFPRegsV8( 0
1416 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, DebugLoc &DL, ----
1417 const LivePhysRegs &LiveRegs, SmallVectorImpl &ScratchRegs) { ----
1418 ----
1419 // Store an available register for FPSCR clearing ----
1420 assert(!ScratchRegs.empty()); 0
1421 unsigned SpareReg = ScratchRegs.front(); 0
1422 ----
1423 // save space on stack for VLSTM ----
1424 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tSUBspi), ARM::SP) 0
1425 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1426 .addImm(CMSE_FP_SAVE_SIZE >> 2) 0
1427 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1428 ----
1429 // Use ScratchRegs to store the fp regs ----
1430 std::vector> ClearedFPRegs; 0
1431 std::vector NonclearedFPRegs; 0
1432 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MBBI->operands()) { 0
1433 if (Op.isReg() && Op.isUse()) { 0
1434 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1435 assert(!ARM::DPRRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
1436 ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)); ----
1437 assert(!ARM::QPRRegClass.contains(Reg)); 0
1438 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1439 if (ScratchRegs.size() >= 2) { 0
1440 unsigned SaveReg2 = ScratchRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1441 unsigned SaveReg1 = ScratchRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1442 ClearedFPRegs.emplace_back(Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2); 0
1443 ----
1444 // Save the fp register to the normal registers ----
1445 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVRRD)) 0
1446 .addReg(SaveReg1, RegState::Define) 0
1447 .addReg(SaveReg2, RegState::Define) 0
1448 .addReg(Reg) 0
1449 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1450 } else { ----
1451 NonclearedFPRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1452 } ----
1453 } else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1454 if (ScratchRegs.size() >= 1) { 0
1455 unsigned SaveReg = ScratchRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1456 ClearedFPRegs.emplace_back(Reg, SaveReg, 0); 0
1457 ----
1458 // Save the fp register to the normal registers ----
1459 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVRS), SaveReg) 0
1460 .addReg(Reg) 0
1461 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1462 } else { ----
1463 NonclearedFPRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1464 } ----
1465 } ----
1466 } ----
1467 } ----
1468 ----
1469 bool passesFPReg = (!NonclearedFPRegs.empty() || !ClearedFPRegs.empty()); 0
1470 ----
1471 if (passesFPReg) 0
1472 assert(STI->hasFPRegs() && "Subtarget needs fpregs"); 0
1473 ----
1474 // Lazy store all fp registers to the stack. ----
1475 // This executes as NOP in the absence of floating-point support. ----
1476 MachineInstrBuilder VLSTM = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLSTM)) 0
1477 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1478 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1479 for (auto R : {ARM::VPR, ARM::FPSCR, ARM::FPSCR_NZCV, ARM::Q0, ARM::Q1, 0
1480 ARM::Q2, ARM::Q3, ARM::Q4, ARM::Q5, ARM::Q6, ARM::Q7}) 0
1481 VLSTM.addReg(R, RegState::Implicit | 0
1482 (LiveRegs.contains(R) ? 0 : RegState::Undef)); 0
1483 ----
1484 // Restore all arguments ----
1485 for (const auto &Regs : ClearedFPRegs) { 0
1486 unsigned Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2; ----
1487 std::tie(Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2) = Regs; 0
1488 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1489 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVDRR), Reg) 0
1490 .addReg(SaveReg1) 0
1491 .addReg(SaveReg2) 0
1492 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1493 else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1494 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVSR), Reg) 0
1495 .addReg(SaveReg1) 0
1496 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1497 } ----
1498 ----
1499 for (unsigned Reg : NonclearedFPRegs) { 0
1500 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1501 if (STI->isLittle()) { 0
1502 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLDRD), Reg) 0
1503 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1504 .addImm((Reg - ARM::D0) * 2) 0
1505 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1506 } else { ----
1507 // For big-endian targets we need to load the two subregisters of Reg ----
1508 // manually because VLDRD would load them in wrong order ----
1509 unsigned SReg0 = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::ssub_0); 0
1510 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLDRS), SReg0) 0
1511 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1512 .addImm((Reg - ARM::D0) * 2) 0
1513 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1514 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLDRS), SReg0 + 1) 0
1515 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1516 .addImm((Reg - ARM::D0) * 2 + 1) 0
1517 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1518 } ----
1519 } else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1520 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLDRS), Reg) 0
1521 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1522 .addImm(Reg - ARM::S0) 0
1523 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1524 } ----
1525 } ----
1526 // restore FPSCR from stack and clear bits 0-4, 7, 28-31 ----
1527 // The other bits are program global according to the AAPCS ----
1528 if (passesFPReg) { 0
1529 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tLDRspi), SpareReg) 0
1530 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1531 .addImm(0x10) 0
1532 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1533 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2BICri), SpareReg) 0
1534 .addReg(SpareReg) 0
1535 .addImm(0x0000009F) 0
1536 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1537 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
1538 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2BICri), SpareReg) 0
1539 .addReg(SpareReg) 0
1540 .addImm(0xF0000000) 0
1541 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1542 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
1543 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMSR)) 0
1544 .addReg(SpareReg) 0
1545 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1546 // The ldr must happen after a floating point instruction. To prevent the ----
1547 // post-ra scheduler to mess with the order, we create a bundle. ----
1548 finalizeBundle(MBB, VLSTM->getIterator(), MBBI->getIterator()); 0
1549 } ----
1550 } 0
1551 ----
1552 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSESaveClearFPRegsV81(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1553 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1554 DebugLoc &DL, ----
1555 const LivePhysRegs &LiveRegs) { ----
1556 BitVector ClearRegs(32, true); 0
1557 bool DefFP = determineFPRegsToClear(*MBBI, ClearRegs); 0
1558 ----
1559 // If the instruction does not write to a FP register and no elements were ----
1560 // removed from the set, then no FP registers were used to pass ----
1561 // arguments/returns. ----
1562 if (!DefFP && ClearRegs.count() == ClearRegs.size()) { 0
1563 // save space on stack for VLSTM ----
1564 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tSUBspi), ARM::SP) 0
1565 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1566 .addImm(CMSE_FP_SAVE_SIZE >> 2) 0
1567 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1568 ----
1569 // Lazy store all FP registers to the stack ----
1570 MachineInstrBuilder VLSTM = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLSTM)) 0
1571 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1572 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1573 for (auto R : {ARM::VPR, ARM::FPSCR, ARM::FPSCR_NZCV, ARM::Q0, ARM::Q1, 0
1574 ARM::Q2, ARM::Q3, ARM::Q4, ARM::Q5, ARM::Q6, ARM::Q7}) 0
1575 VLSTM.addReg(R, RegState::Implicit | 0
1576 (LiveRegs.contains(R) ? 0 : RegState::Undef)); 0
1577 } else { ----
1578 // Push all the callee-saved registers (s16-s31). ----
1579 MachineInstrBuilder VPUSH = ----
1580 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VSTMSDB_UPD), ARM::SP) 0
1581 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1582 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1583 for (int Reg = ARM::S16; Reg <= ARM::S31; ++Reg) 0
1584 VPUSH.addReg(Reg); 0
1585 ----
1586 // Clear FP registers with a VSCCLRM. ----
1587 (void)CMSEClearFPRegsV81(MBB, MBBI, ClearRegs); 0
1588 ----
1589 // Save floating-point context. ----
1590 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VSTR_FPCXTS_pre), ARM::SP) 0
1591 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1592 .addImm(-8) 0
1593 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1594 } ----
1595 } 0
1596 ----
1597 // Restore FP registers if present ----
1598 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSERestoreFPRegs( 0
1599 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, DebugLoc &DL, ----
1600 SmallVectorImpl &AvailableRegs) { ----
1601 if (STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps()) 0
1602 CMSERestoreFPRegsV81(MBB, MBBI, DL, AvailableRegs); 0
1603 else if (STI->hasV8MMainlineOps()) 0
1604 CMSERestoreFPRegsV8(MBB, MBBI, DL, AvailableRegs); 0
1605 } 0
1606 ----
1607 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSERestoreFPRegsV8( 0
1608 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, DebugLoc &DL, ----
1609 SmallVectorImpl &AvailableRegs) { ----
1610 ----
1611 // Keep a scratch register for the mitigation sequence. ----
1612 unsigned ScratchReg = ARM::NoRegister; 0
1613 if (STI->fixCMSE_CVE_2021_35465()) 0
1614 ScratchReg = AvailableRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1615 ----
1616 // Use AvailableRegs to store the fp regs ----
1617 std::vector> ClearedFPRegs; 0
1618 std::vector NonclearedFPRegs; 0
1619 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MBBI->operands()) { 0
1620 if (Op.isReg() && Op.isDef()) { 0
1621 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1622 assert(!ARM::DPRRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
1623 ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)); ----
1624 assert(!ARM::QPRRegClass.contains(Reg)); 0
1625 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1626 if (AvailableRegs.size() >= 2) { 0
1627 unsigned SaveReg2 = AvailableRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1628 unsigned SaveReg1 = AvailableRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1629 ClearedFPRegs.emplace_back(Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2); 0
1630 ----
1631 // Save the fp register to the normal registers ----
1632 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVRRD)) 0
1633 .addReg(SaveReg1, RegState::Define) 0
1634 .addReg(SaveReg2, RegState::Define) 0
1635 .addReg(Reg) 0
1636 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1637 } else { ----
1638 NonclearedFPRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1639 } ----
1640 } else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
1641 if (AvailableRegs.size() >= 1) { 0
1642 unsigned SaveReg = AvailableRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1643 ClearedFPRegs.emplace_back(Reg, SaveReg, 0); 0
1644 ----
1645 // Save the fp register to the normal registers ----
1646 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVRS), SaveReg) 0
1647 .addReg(Reg) 0
1648 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1649 } else { ----
1650 NonclearedFPRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1651 } ----
1652 } ----
1653 } ----
1654 } ----
1655 ----
1656 bool returnsFPReg = (!NonclearedFPRegs.empty() || !ClearedFPRegs.empty()); 0
1657 ----
1658 if (returnsFPReg) 0
1659 assert(STI->hasFPRegs() && "Subtarget needs fpregs"); 0
1660 ----
1661 // Push FP regs that cannot be restored via normal registers on the stack ----
1662 for (unsigned Reg : NonclearedFPRegs) { 0
1663 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1664 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VSTRD)) 0
1665 .addReg(Reg) 0
1666 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1667 .addImm((Reg - ARM::D0) * 2) 0
1668 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1669 else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1670 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VSTRS)) 0
1671 .addReg(Reg) 0
1672 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1673 .addImm(Reg - ARM::S0) 0
1674 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1675 } ----
1676 ----
1677 // Lazy load fp regs from stack. ----
1678 // This executes as NOP in the absence of floating-point support. ----
1679 MachineInstrBuilder VLLDM = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLLDM)) 0
1680 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1681 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1682 ----
1683 if (STI->fixCMSE_CVE_2021_35465()) { 0
1684 auto Bundler = MIBundleBuilder(MBB, VLLDM); 0
1685 // Read the CONTROL register. ----
1686 Bundler.append(BuildMI(*MBB.getParent(), DL, TII->get(ARM::t2MRS_M)) 0
1687 .addReg(ScratchReg, RegState::Define) 0
1688 .addImm(20) 0
1689 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL))); 0
1690 // Check bit 3 (SFPA). ----
1691 Bundler.append(BuildMI(*MBB.getParent(), DL, TII->get(ARM::t2TSTri)) 0
1692 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1693 .addImm(8) 0
1694 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL))); 0
1695 // Emit the IT block. ----
1696 Bundler.append(BuildMI(*MBB.getParent(), DL, TII->get(ARM::t2IT)) 0
1697 .addImm(ARMCC::NE) 0
1698 .addImm(8)); 0
1699 // If SFPA is clear jump over to VLLDM, otherwise execute an instruction ----
1700 // which has no functional effect apart from causing context creation: ----
1701 // vmovne s0, s0. In the absence of FPU we emit .inst.w 0xeeb00a40, ----
1702 // which is defined as NOP if not executed. ----
1703 if (STI->hasFPRegs()) 0
1704 Bundler.append(BuildMI(*MBB.getParent(), DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVS)) 0
1705 .addReg(ARM::S0, RegState::Define) 0
1706 .addReg(ARM::S0, RegState::Undef) 0
1707 .add(predOps(ARMCC::NE))); 0
1708 else ----
1709 Bundler.append(BuildMI(*MBB.getParent(), DL, TII->get(ARM::INLINEASM)) 0
1710 .addExternalSymbol(".inst.w 0xeeb00a40") 0
1711 .addImm(InlineAsm::Extra_HasSideEffects)); 0
1712 finalizeBundle(MBB, Bundler.begin(), Bundler.end()); 0
1713 } ----
1714 ----
1715 // Restore all FP registers via normal registers ----
1716 for (const auto &Regs : ClearedFPRegs) { 0
1717 unsigned Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2; ----
1718 std::tie(Reg, SaveReg1, SaveReg2) = Regs; 0
1719 if (ARM::DPR_VFP2RegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1720 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVDRR), Reg) 0
1721 .addReg(SaveReg1) 0
1722 .addReg(SaveReg2) 0
1723 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1724 else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
1725 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VMOVSR), Reg) 0
1726 .addReg(SaveReg1) 0
1727 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1728 } ----
1729 ----
1730 // Pop the stack space ----
1731 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tADDspi), ARM::SP) 0
1732 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1733 .addImm(CMSE_FP_SAVE_SIZE >> 2) 0
1734 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1735 } 0
1736 ----
1737 static bool definesOrUsesFPReg(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1738 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.operands()) { 0
1739 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1740 continue; 0
1741 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1742 if ((Reg >= ARM::Q0 && Reg <= ARM::Q7) || 0
1743 (Reg >= ARM::D0 && Reg <= ARM::D15) || 0
1744 (Reg >= ARM::S0 && Reg <= ARM::S31)) 0
1745 return true; 0
1746 } ----
1747 return false; 0
1748 } ----
1749 ----
1750 void ARMExpandPseudo::CMSERestoreFPRegsV81( 0
1751 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, DebugLoc &DL, ----
1752 SmallVectorImpl &AvailableRegs) { ----
1753 if (!definesOrUsesFPReg(*MBBI)) { 0
1754 if (STI->fixCMSE_CVE_2021_35465()) { 0
1755 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VSCCLRMS)) 0
1756 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
1757 .addReg(ARM::VPR, RegState::Define); 0
1758 } ----
1759 ----
1760 // Load FP registers from stack. ----
1761 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLLDM)) 0
1762 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1763 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1764 ----
1765 // Pop the stack space ----
1766 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tADDspi), ARM::SP) 0
1767 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1768 .addImm(CMSE_FP_SAVE_SIZE >> 2) 0
1769 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1770 } else { ----
1771 // Restore the floating point context. ----
1772 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::VLDR_FPCXTS_post), 0
1773 ARM::SP) ----
1774 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1775 .addImm(8) 0
1776 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1777 ----
1778 // Pop all the callee-saved registers (s16-s31). ----
1779 MachineInstrBuilder VPOP = ----
1780 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::VLDMSIA_UPD), ARM::SP) 0
1781 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
1782 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1783 for (int Reg = ARM::S16; Reg <= ARM::S31; ++Reg) 0
1784 VPOP.addReg(Reg, RegState::Define); 0
1785 } ----
1786 } 0
1787 ----
1788 /// Expand a CMP_SWAP pseudo-inst to an ldrex/strex loop as simply as ----
1789 /// possible. This only gets used at -O0 so we don't care about efficiency of ----
1790 /// the generated code. ----
1791 bool ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandCMP_SWAP(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1792 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1793 unsigned LdrexOp, unsigned StrexOp, ----
1794 unsigned UxtOp, ----
1795 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
1796 bool IsThumb = STI->isThumb(); 0
1797 bool IsThumb1Only = STI->isThumb1Only(); 0
1798 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1799 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1800 const MachineOperand &Dest = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1801 Register TempReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1802 // Duplicating undef operands into 2 instructions does not guarantee the same ----
1803 // value on both; However undef should be replaced by xzr anyway. ----
1804 assert(!MI.getOperand(2).isUndef() && "cannot handle undef"); 0
1805 Register AddrReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1806 Register DesiredReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1807 Register NewReg = MI.getOperand(4).getReg(); 0
1808 ----
1809 if (IsThumb) { 0
1810 assert(STI->hasV8MBaselineOps() && 0
1811 "CMP_SWAP not expected to be custom expanded for Thumb1"); ----
1812 assert((UxtOp == 0 || UxtOp == ARM::tUXTB || UxtOp == ARM::tUXTH) && 0
1813 "ARMv8-M.baseline does not have t2UXTB/t2UXTH"); ----
1814 assert((UxtOp == 0 || ARM::tGPRRegClass.contains(DesiredReg)) && 0
1815 "DesiredReg used for UXT op must be tGPR"); ----
1816 } ----
1817 ----
1818 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
1819 auto LoadCmpBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1820 auto StoreBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1821 auto DoneBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1822 ----
1823 MF->insert(++MBB.getIterator(), LoadCmpBB); 0
1824 MF->insert(++LoadCmpBB->getIterator(), StoreBB); 0
1825 MF->insert(++StoreBB->getIterator(), DoneBB); 0
1826 ----
1827 if (UxtOp) { 0
1828 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1829 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(UxtOp), DesiredReg) 0
1830 .addReg(DesiredReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1831 if (!IsThumb) 0
1832 MIB.addImm(0); 0
1833 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1834 } ----
1835 ----
1836 // .Lloadcmp: ----
1837 // ldrex rDest, [rAddr] ----
1838 // cmp rDest, rDesired ----
1839 // bne .Ldone ----
1840 ----
1841 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
1842 MIB = BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(LdrexOp), Dest.getReg()); 0
1843 MIB.addReg(AddrReg); 0
1844 if (LdrexOp == ARM::t2LDREX) 0
1845 MIB.addImm(0); // a 32-bit Thumb ldrex (only) allows an offset. 0
1846 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1847 ----
1848 unsigned CMPrr = IsThumb ? ARM::tCMPhir : ARM::CMPrr; 0
1849 BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(CMPrr)) 0
1850 .addReg(Dest.getReg(), getKillRegState(Dest.isDead())) 0
1851 .addReg(DesiredReg) 0
1852 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1853 unsigned Bcc = IsThumb ? ARM::tBcc : ARM::Bcc; 0
1854 BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(Bcc)) 0
1855 .addMBB(DoneBB) 0
1856 .addImm(ARMCC::NE) 0
1857 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
1858 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
1859 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(StoreBB); 0
1860 ----
1861 // .Lstore: ----
1862 // strex rTempReg, rNew, [rAddr] ----
1863 // cmp rTempReg, #0 ----
1864 // bne .Lloadcmp ----
1865 MIB = BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(StrexOp), TempReg) 0
1866 .addReg(NewReg) 0
1867 .addReg(AddrReg); 0
1868 if (StrexOp == ARM::t2STREX) 0
1869 MIB.addImm(0); // a 32-bit Thumb strex (only) allows an offset. 0
1870 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1871 ----
1872 unsigned CMPri = 0
1873 IsThumb ? (IsThumb1Only ? ARM::tCMPi8 : ARM::t2CMPri) : ARM::CMPri; 0
1874 BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(CMPri)) 0
1875 .addReg(TempReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1876 .addImm(0) 0
1877 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1878 BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(Bcc)) 0
1879 .addMBB(LoadCmpBB) 0
1880 .addImm(ARMCC::NE) 0
1881 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
1882 StoreBB->addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
1883 StoreBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
1884 ----
1885 DoneBB->splice(DoneBB->end(), &MBB, MI, MBB.end()); 0
1886 DoneBB->transferSuccessors(&MBB); 0
1887 ----
1888 MBB.addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
1889 ----
1890 NextMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
1891 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1892 ----
1893 // Recompute livein lists. ----
1894 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs; 0
1895 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *DoneBB); 0
1896 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
1897 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
1898 // Do an extra pass around the loop to get loop carried registers right. ----
1899 StoreBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
1900 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
1901 LoadCmpBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
1902 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
1903 ----
1904 return true; 0
1905 } 0
1906 ----
1907 /// ARM's ldrexd/strexd take a consecutive register pair (represented as a ----
1908 /// single GPRPair register), Thumb's take two separate registers so we need to ----
1909 /// extract the subregs from the pair. ----
1910 static void addExclusiveRegPair(MachineInstrBuilder &MIB, MachineOperand &Reg, 0
1911 unsigned Flags, bool IsThumb, ----
1912 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1913 if (IsThumb) { 0
1914 Register RegLo = TRI->getSubReg(Reg.getReg(), ARM::gsub_0); 0
1915 Register RegHi = TRI->getSubReg(Reg.getReg(), ARM::gsub_1); 0
1916 MIB.addReg(RegLo, Flags); 0
1917 MIB.addReg(RegHi, Flags); 0
1918 } else ----
1919 MIB.addReg(Reg.getReg(), Flags); 0
1920 } 0
1921 ----
1922 /// Expand a 64-bit CMP_SWAP to an ldrexd/strexd loop. ----
1923 bool ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandCMP_SWAP_64(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1924 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1925 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
1926 bool IsThumb = STI->isThumb(); 0
1927 assert(!STI->isThumb1Only() && "CMP_SWAP_64 unsupported under Thumb1!"); 0
1928 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1929 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1930 MachineOperand &Dest = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1931 Register TempReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1932 // Duplicating undef operands into 2 instructions does not guarantee the same ----
1933 // value on both; However undef should be replaced by xzr anyway. ----
1934 assert(!MI.getOperand(2).isUndef() && "cannot handle undef"); 0
1935 Register AddrReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1936 Register DesiredReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1937 MachineOperand New = MI.getOperand(4); 0
1938 New.setIsKill(false); 0
1939 ----
1940 Register DestLo = TRI->getSubReg(Dest.getReg(), ARM::gsub_0); 0
1941 Register DestHi = TRI->getSubReg(Dest.getReg(), ARM::gsub_1); 0
1942 Register DesiredLo = TRI->getSubReg(DesiredReg, ARM::gsub_0); 0
1943 Register DesiredHi = TRI->getSubReg(DesiredReg, ARM::gsub_1); 0
1944 ----
1945 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
1946 auto LoadCmpBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1947 auto StoreBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1948 auto DoneBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
1949 ----
1950 MF->insert(++MBB.getIterator(), LoadCmpBB); 0
1951 MF->insert(++LoadCmpBB->getIterator(), StoreBB); 0
1952 MF->insert(++StoreBB->getIterator(), DoneBB); 0
1953 ----
1954 // .Lloadcmp: ----
1955 // ldrexd rDestLo, rDestHi, [rAddr] ----
1956 // cmp rDestLo, rDesiredLo ----
1957 // sbcs dead rTempReg, rDestHi, rDesiredHi ----
1958 // bne .Ldone ----
1959 unsigned LDREXD = IsThumb ? ARM::t2LDREXD : ARM::LDREXD; 0
1960 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
1961 MIB = BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(LDREXD)); 0
1962 addExclusiveRegPair(MIB, Dest, RegState::Define, IsThumb, TRI); 0
1963 MIB.addReg(AddrReg).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1964 ----
1965 unsigned CMPrr = IsThumb ? ARM::tCMPhir : ARM::CMPrr; 0
1966 BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(CMPrr)) 0
1967 .addReg(DestLo, getKillRegState(Dest.isDead())) 0
1968 .addReg(DesiredLo) 0
1969 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1970 ----
1971 BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(CMPrr)) 0
1972 .addReg(DestHi, getKillRegState(Dest.isDead())) 0
1973 .addReg(DesiredHi) 0
1974 .addImm(ARMCC::EQ).addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
1975 ----
1976 unsigned Bcc = IsThumb ? ARM::tBcc : ARM::Bcc; 0
1977 BuildMI(LoadCmpBB, DL, TII->get(Bcc)) 0
1978 .addMBB(DoneBB) 0
1979 .addImm(ARMCC::NE) 0
1980 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
1981 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
1982 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(StoreBB); 0
1983 ----
1984 // .Lstore: ----
1985 // strexd rTempReg, rNewLo, rNewHi, [rAddr] ----
1986 // cmp rTempReg, #0 ----
1987 // bne .Lloadcmp ----
1988 unsigned STREXD = IsThumb ? ARM::t2STREXD : ARM::STREXD; 0
1989 MIB = BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(STREXD), TempReg); 0
1990 unsigned Flags = getKillRegState(New.isDead()); 0
1991 addExclusiveRegPair(MIB, New, Flags, IsThumb, TRI); 0
1992 MIB.addReg(AddrReg).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1993 ----
1994 unsigned CMPri = IsThumb ? ARM::t2CMPri : ARM::CMPri; 0
1995 BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(CMPri)) 0
1996 .addReg(TempReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1997 .addImm(0) 0
1998 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1999 BuildMI(StoreBB, DL, TII->get(Bcc)) 0
2000 .addMBB(LoadCmpBB) 0
2001 .addImm(ARMCC::NE) 0
2002 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Kill); 0
2003 StoreBB->addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
2004 StoreBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
2005 ----
2006 DoneBB->splice(DoneBB->end(), &MBB, MI, MBB.end()); 0
2007 DoneBB->transferSuccessors(&MBB); 0
2008 ----
2009 MBB.addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
2010 ----
2011 NextMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
2012 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
2013 ----
2014 // Recompute livein lists. ----
2015 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs; 0
2016 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *DoneBB); 0
2017 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
2018 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
2019 // Do an extra pass around the loop to get loop carried registers right. ----
2020 StoreBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
2021 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
2022 LoadCmpBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
2023 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
2024 ----
2025 return true; 0
2026 } 0
2027 ----
2028 static void CMSEPushCalleeSaves(const TargetInstrInfo &TII, 0
2029 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
2030 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, int JumpReg, ----
2031 const LivePhysRegs &LiveRegs, bool Thumb1Only) { ----
2032 const DebugLoc &DL = MBBI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2033 if (Thumb1Only) { // push Lo and Hi regs separately 0
2034 MachineInstrBuilder PushMIB = ----
2035 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tPUSH)).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2036 for (int Reg = ARM::R4; Reg < ARM::R8; ++Reg) { 0
2037 PushMIB.addReg( 0
2038 Reg, Reg == JumpReg || LiveRegs.contains(Reg) ? 0 : RegState::Undef); 0
2039 } ----
2040 ----
2041 // Thumb1 can only tPUSH low regs, so we copy the high regs to the low ----
2042 // regs that we just saved and push the low regs again, taking care to ----
2043 // not clobber JumpReg. If JumpReg is one of the low registers, push first ----
2044 // the values of r9-r11, and then r8. That would leave them ordered in ----
2045 // memory, and allow us to later pop them with a single instructions. ----
2046 // FIXME: Could also use any of r0-r3 that are free (including in the ----
2047 // first PUSH above). ----
2048 for (int LoReg = ARM::R7, HiReg = ARM::R11; LoReg >= ARM::R4; --LoReg) { 0
2049 if (JumpReg == LoReg) 0
2050 continue; 0
2051 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tMOVr), LoReg) 0
2052 .addReg(HiReg, LiveRegs.contains(HiReg) ? 0 : RegState::Undef) 0
2053 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2054 --HiReg; 0
2055 } ----
2056 MachineInstrBuilder PushMIB2 = ----
2057 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tPUSH)).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2058 for (int Reg = ARM::R4; Reg < ARM::R8; ++Reg) { 0
2059 if (Reg == JumpReg) 0
2060 continue; 0
2061 PushMIB2.addReg(Reg, RegState::Kill); 0
2062 } ----
2063 ----
2064 // If we couldn't use a low register for temporary storage (because it was ----
2065 // the JumpReg), use r4 or r5, whichever is not JumpReg. It has already been ----
2066 // saved. ----
2067 if (JumpReg >= ARM::R4 && JumpReg <= ARM::R7) { 0
2068 int LoReg = JumpReg == ARM::R4 ? ARM::R5 : ARM::R4; 0
2069 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tMOVr), LoReg) 0
2070 .addReg(ARM::R8, LiveRegs.contains(ARM::R8) ? 0 : RegState::Undef) 0
2071 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2072 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tPUSH)) 0
2073 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2074 .addReg(LoReg, RegState::Kill); 0
2075 } ----
2076 } else { // push Lo and Hi registers with a single instruction ----
2077 MachineInstrBuilder PushMIB = ----
2078 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::t2STMDB_UPD), ARM::SP) 0
2079 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
2080 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2081 for (int Reg = ARM::R4; Reg < ARM::R12; ++Reg) { 0
2082 PushMIB.addReg( 0
2083 Reg, Reg == JumpReg || LiveRegs.contains(Reg) ? 0 : RegState::Undef); 0
2084 } ----
2085 } ----
2086 } 0
2087 ----
2088 static void CMSEPopCalleeSaves(const TargetInstrInfo &TII, 0
2089 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
2090 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, int JumpReg, ----
2091 bool Thumb1Only) { ----
2092 const DebugLoc &DL = MBBI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2093 if (Thumb1Only) { 0
2094 MachineInstrBuilder PopMIB = ----
2095 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tPOP)).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2096 for (int R = 0; R < 4; ++R) { 0
2097 PopMIB.addReg(ARM::R4 + R, RegState::Define); 0
2098 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tMOVr), ARM::R8 + R) 0
2099 .addReg(ARM::R4 + R, RegState::Kill) 0
2100 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2101 } ----
2102 MachineInstrBuilder PopMIB2 = ----
2103 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::tPOP)).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2104 for (int R = 0; R < 4; ++R) 0
2105 PopMIB2.addReg(ARM::R4 + R, RegState::Define); 0
2106 } else { // pop Lo and Hi registers with a single instruction ----
2107 MachineInstrBuilder PopMIB = ----
2108 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII.get(ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD), ARM::SP) 0
2109 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
2110 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2111 for (int Reg = ARM::R4; Reg < ARM::R12; ++Reg) 0
2112 PopMIB.addReg(Reg, RegState::Define); 0
2113 } ----
2114 } 0
2115 ----
2116 bool ARMExpandPseudo::ExpandMI(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
2117 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
2118 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
2119 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2120 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2121 switch (Opcode) { 0
2122 default: 0
2123 return false; 0
2124 ----
2125 case ARM::VBSPd: 0
2126 case ARM::VBSPq: { ----
2127 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2128 if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(3).getReg()) { 0
2129 // Expand to VBIT ----
2130 unsigned NewOpc = Opcode == ARM::VBSPd ? ARM::VBITd : ARM::VBITq; 0
2131 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
2132 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
2133 .add(MI.getOperand(3)) 0
2134 .add(MI.getOperand(2)) 0
2135 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2136 .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm()) 0
2137 .add(MI.getOperand(5)); 0
2138 } else if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(2).getReg()) { 0
2139 // Expand to VBIF ----
2140 unsigned NewOpc = Opcode == ARM::VBSPd ? ARM::VBIFd : ARM::VBIFq; 0
2141 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
2142 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
2143 .add(MI.getOperand(2)) 0
2144 .add(MI.getOperand(3)) 0
2145 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2146 .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm()) 0
2147 .add(MI.getOperand(5)); 0
2148 } else { ----
2149 // Expand to VBSL ----
2150 unsigned NewOpc = Opcode == ARM::VBSPd ? ARM::VBSLd : ARM::VBSLq; 0
2151 if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) { 0
2152 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
2153 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
2154 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2155 .add(MI.getOperand(2)) 0
2156 .add(MI.getOperand(3)) 0
2157 .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm()) 0
2158 .add(MI.getOperand(5)); 0
2159 } else { ----
2160 // Use move to satisfy constraints ----
2161 unsigned MoveOpc = Opcode == ARM::VBSPd ? ARM::VORRd : ARM::VORRq; 0
2162 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(MoveOpc)) 0
2163 .addReg(DstReg, 0
2164 RegState::Define | ----
2165 getRenamableRegState(MI.getOperand(0).isRenamable())) 0
2166 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2167 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2168 .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm()) 0
2169 .add(MI.getOperand(5)); 0
2170 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
2171 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
2172 .addReg(DstReg, 0
2173 RegState::Kill | ----
2174 getRenamableRegState(MI.getOperand(0).isRenamable())) 0
2175 .add(MI.getOperand(2)) 0
2176 .add(MI.getOperand(3)) 0
2177 .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm()) 0
2178 .add(MI.getOperand(5)); 0
2179 } ----
2180 } ----
2181 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
2182 return true; 0
2183 } ----
2184 ----
2185 case ARM::TCRETURNdi: 0
2186 case ARM::TCRETURNri: { ----
2187 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
2188 if (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::SEH_EpilogEnd) 0
2189 MBBI--; 0
2190 if (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::SEH_Nop_Ret) 0
2191 MBBI--; 0
2192 assert(MBBI->isReturn() && 0
2193 "Can only insert epilog into returning blocks"); ----
2194 unsigned RetOpcode = MBBI->getOpcode(); 0
2195 DebugLoc dl = MBBI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2196 const ARMBaseInstrInfo &TII = *static_cast( ----
2197 MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()); 0
2198 ----
2199 // Tail call return: adjust the stack pointer and jump to callee. ----
2200 MBBI = MBB.getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
2201 if (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::SEH_EpilogEnd) 0
2202 MBBI--; 0
2203 if (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::SEH_Nop_Ret) 0
2204 MBBI--; 0
2205 MachineOperand &JumpTarget = MBBI->getOperand(0); 0
2206 ----
2207 // Jump to label or value in register. ----
2208 if (RetOpcode == ARM::TCRETURNdi) { 0
2209 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
2210 bool NeedsWinCFI = MF->getTarget().getMCAsmInfo()->usesWindowsCFI() && 0
2211 MF->getFunction().needsUnwindTableEntry(); 0
2212 unsigned TCOpcode = ----
2213 STI->isThumb() 0
2214 ? ((STI->isTargetMachO() || NeedsWinCFI) ? ARM::tTAILJMPd 0
2215 : ARM::tTAILJMPdND) ----
2216 : ARM::TAILJMPd; 0

2218 if (JumpTarget.isGlobal()) 0
2219 MIB.addGlobalAddress(JumpTarget.getGlobal(), JumpTarget.getOffset(), 0
2220 JumpTarget.getTargetFlags()); ----
2221 else { ----
2222 assert(JumpTarget.isSymbol()); 0
2223 MIB.addExternalSymbol(JumpTarget.getSymbolName(), 0
2224 JumpTarget.getTargetFlags()); ----
2225 } ----
2226 ----
2227 // Add the default predicate in Thumb mode. ----
2228 if (STI->isThumb()) 0
2229 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2230 } else if (RetOpcode == ARM::TCRETURNri) { 0

2232 STI->isThumb() ? ARM::tTAILJMPr 0
2233 : (STI->hasV4TOps() ? ARM::TAILJMPr : ARM::TAILJMPr4); 0
2234 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, dl, 0
2235 TII.get(Opcode)) ----
2236 .addReg(JumpTarget.getReg(), RegState::Kill); 0
2237 } ----
2238 ----
2239 auto NewMI = std::prev(MBBI); 0
2240 for (unsigned i = 2, e = MBBI->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
2241 NewMI->addOperand(MBBI->getOperand(i)); 0
2242 ----
2243 ----
2244 // Update call site info and delete the pseudo instruction TCRETURN. ----
2245 if (MI.isCandidateForCallSiteEntry()) 0
2246 MI.getMF()->moveCallSiteInfo(&MI, &*NewMI); 0
2247 // Copy nomerge flag over to new instruction. ----
2248 if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::NoMerge)) 0
2249 NewMI->setFlag(MachineInstr::NoMerge); 0
2250 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
2251 ----
2252 MBBI = NewMI; 0
2253 return true; 0
2254 } 0
2255 case ARM::tBXNS_RET: { 0
2256 // For v8.0-M.Main we need to authenticate LR before clearing FPRs, which ----
2257 // uses R12 as a scratch register. ----
2258 if (!STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps() && AFI->shouldSignReturnAddress()) 0
2259 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::t2AUT)); 0
2260 ----
2261 MachineBasicBlock &AfterBB = CMSEClearFPRegs(MBB, MBBI); 0
2262 ----
2263 if (STI->hasV8_1MMainlineOps()) { 0
2264 // Restore the non-secure floating point context. ----
2265 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), 0
2266 TII->get(ARM::VLDR_FPCXTNS_post), ARM::SP) 0
2267 .addReg(ARM::SP) 0
2268 .addImm(4) 0
2269 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2270 ----
2271 if (AFI->shouldSignReturnAddress()) 0
2272 BuildMI(AfterBB, AfterBB.end(), DebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::t2AUT)); 0
2273 } ----
2274 ----
2275 // Clear all GPR that are not a use of the return instruction. ----
2276 assert(llvm::all_of(MBBI->operands(), [](const MachineOperand &Op) { 0
2277 return !Op.isReg() || Op.getReg() != ARM::R12; ----
2278 })); ----
2279 SmallVector ClearRegs; 0
2280 determineGPRegsToClear( 0
2281 *MBBI, {ARM::R0, ARM::R1, ARM::R2, ARM::R3, ARM::R12}, ClearRegs); 0
2282 CMSEClearGPRegs(AfterBB, AfterBB.end(), MBBI->getDebugLoc(), ClearRegs, 0
2283 ARM::LR); ----

2285 MachineInstrBuilder NewMI = ----

2287 TII->get(ARM::tBXNS)) 0

2289 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0

2291 NewMI->addOperand(Op); 0

2294 } 0
2295 case ARM::tBLXNS_CALL: { 0
2296 DebugLoc DL = MBBI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2297 Register JumpReg = MBBI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2298 ----
2299 // Figure out which registers are live at the point immediately before the ----
2300 // call. When we indiscriminately push a set of registers, the live ----
2301 // registers are added as ordinary use operands, whereas dead registers ----
2302 // are "undef". ----
2303 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs(*TRI); 0

2306 LiveRegs.stepBackward(MI); 0
2307 LiveRegs.stepBackward(*MBBI); 0

2316 ARM::R10, ARM::R11, ARM::R12}, ----

2321 // We need to use the first so we can ensure it is a low register. ----

2324 // Clear LSB of JumpReg ----
2325 if (AFI->isThumb2Function()) { 0
2326 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::t2BICri), JumpReg) 0
2327 .addReg(JumpReg) 0
2328 .addImm(1) 0
2329 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2330 .add(condCodeOp()); 0

2332 // We need to use an extra register to cope with 8M Baseline, ----
2333 // since we have saved all of the registers we are ok to trash a non ----
2334 // argument register here. ----

2341 .addReg(JumpReg) 0

2344 } ----

2366 } 0

2485 case ARM::Int_eh_sjlj_dispatchsetup: { 0

2491 // pointer) here since eh.sjlj.setjmp and eh.sjlj.longjmp don't do it ----
2492 // for us. Otherwise, expand to nothing. ----

2501 FramePtr, -NumBytes, ARMCC::AL, 0, *TII); 0

2503 emitThumbRegPlusImmediate(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), ARM::R6, 0
2504 FramePtr, -NumBytes, *TII, RI); 0
2505 } else { ----
2506 emitARMRegPlusImmediate(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), ARM::R6, 0
2507 FramePtr, -NumBytes, ARMCC::AL, 0, ----
2508 *TII); 0
2509 } ----
2510 // If there's dynamic realignment, adjust for it. ----
2511 if (RI.hasStackRealignment(MF)) { 0
2512 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
2513 Align MaxAlign = MFI.getMaxAlign(); 0
2514 assert (!AFI->isThumb1OnlyFunction()); 0
2515 // Emit bic r6, r6, MaxAlign ----
2516 assert(MaxAlign <= Align(256) && 0
2517 "The BIC instruction cannot encode " ----
2518 "immediates larger than 256 with all lower " ----
2519 "bits set."); ----
2520 unsigned bicOpc = AFI->isThumbFunction() ? 0
2521 ARM::t2BICri : ARM::BICri; 0
2522 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(bicOpc), ARM::R6) 0
2523 .addReg(ARM::R6, RegState::Kill) 0
2524 .addImm(MaxAlign.value() - 1) 0
2525 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2526 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
2527 } ----
2528 } ----
2529 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
2530 return true; 0
2531 } ----
2532 ----
2533 case ARM::MOVsrl_glue: 0
2534 case ARM::MOVsra_glue: { ----
2535 // These are just fancy MOVs instructions. ----
2536 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::MOVsi), 0
2537 MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
2538 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2539 .addImm(ARM_AM::getSORegOpc( 0
2540 (Opcode == ARM::MOVsrl_glue ? ARM_AM::lsr : ARM_AM::asr), 1)) ----
2541 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2542 .addReg(ARM::CPSR, RegState::Define); 0
2543 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
2544 return true; 0
2545 } ----
2546 case ARM::RRX: { 0
2547 // This encodes as "MOVs Rd, Rm, rrx ----
2548 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::MOVsi), 0
2549 MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
2550 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
2551 .addImm(ARM_AM::getSORegOpc(ARM_AM::rrx, 0)) 0
2552 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2553 .add(condCodeOp()) 0

2558 case ARM::tTPsoft: 0
2559 case ARM::TPsoft: { ----
2560 const bool Thumb = Opcode == ARM::tTPsoft; 0
2561 ----
2562 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
2563 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
2564 if (STI->genLongCalls()) { 0
2565 MachineConstantPool *MCP = MF->getConstantPool(); 0
2566 unsigned PCLabelID = AFI->createPICLabelUId(); 0
2567 MachineConstantPoolValue *CPV = ----
2568 ARMConstantPoolSymbol::Create(MF->getFunction().getContext(), 0
2569 "__aeabi_read_tp", PCLabelID, 0); ----
2570 Register Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2571 MIB = 0
2572 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
2573 TII->get(Thumb ? ARM::tLDRpci : ARM::LDRi12), Reg) 0
2574 .addConstantPoolIndex(MCP->getConstantPoolIndex(CPV, Align(4))); 0
2575 if (!Thumb) 0
2576 MIB.addImm(0); 0
2577 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2578 ----

2581 TII->get(Thumb ? gettBLXrOpcode(*MF) : getBLXOpcode(*MF))); 0
2582 if (Thumb) 0
2583 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2584 MIB.addReg(Reg, RegState::Kill); 0
2585 } else { ----
2586 MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
2587 TII->get(Thumb ? ARM::tBL : ARM::BL)); 0
2588 if (Thumb) 0
2589 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2590 MIB.addExternalSymbol("__aeabi_read_tp", 0); 0
2591 } ----
2592 ----
2593 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
2594 MIB.copyImplicitOps(MI); 0
2595 // Update the call site info. ----
2596 if (MI.isCandidateForCallSiteEntry()) 0
2597 MF->moveCallSiteInfo(&MI, &*MIB); 0
2598 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
2599 return true; 0
2600 } ----
2601 case ARM::tLDRpci_pic: 0
2602 case ARM::t2LDRpci_pic: { ----
2603 unsigned NewLdOpc = (Opcode == ARM::tLDRpci_pic) 0
2604 ? ARM::tLDRpci : ARM::t2LDRpci; 0
2605 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2606 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
2607 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewLdOpc), DstReg) 0
2608 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
